in Miami we have two seasons. hot as fuck. and hot.

other places have seasons. four clear, external markers  of change and impermanence. 
heartache in that hot, heavy summer. cutting your hair and cutting ties when leaves changes in the fall. 

here one must remind oneself.  i have turned to ice in this heat, and then gone back to water too. 
i‚Äôve gone through winters and summers this year . and spring visited me when i learned to let go.  sometimes these things happened all in one day. 

thank you 2023 
see you in 2024
